An Act relative to unemployment insurance.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 24 of Chapter 151A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended in subsection (a) by striking out in lines 3 and 4 the words
3 “Have been paid wages in the base period amounting to at least thirty times the weekly benefit
4 rate” and inserting in place thereof the following:-
5 "Have been paid wages in at least two-quarters of the base period amounting to at least
6 thirty times the weekly benefit rate".
7 SECTION 2. Section 6 of Chapter 175M of the General Laws as appearing is hereby
8 amended in subsection (2)(d) by striking "25 employees" and inserting in place thereof the
9 following:-- "50 employees".
